<TITLE> Football camp resumes after Salahuddin intervenes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 27 (bdnews24.com)  The camp of the national football team resumes on Tuesday at the Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan after BFF president Kazi Salahuddin on Monday intervened to solve the walkout drama of eight national footballers. "All problems are solved and we have now no problem," Salahuddin told reporters after having meetings with Brazilian coach Edson Silva Dido and eight footballers, who walked out of training on Thursday citing 'unbearable' training. "Players made mistakes and apologised to the coach, who is also accepted those players in his camp. The coach is staying with us and the players are also going back to the camp from Tuesday," said Salahuddin, who sat with the coach and the players coming straight from the airport after returning home from Thailand. The players were fined a month's salary and the coach warned by the National Team Management Committee on Sunday. "One thing has to be realised that the coach is the head of the team and nobody is bigger than the coach," said the BFF boss. Eight players  Rajani Kanta Barman, Arman Aziz, Jahid Hasan Emily, Jahid Hossain, Wali Faisal, Jahed Parvez Chowdhury, Arif Hossain and Mofazzal Hossain Saikat -- walked out of Dido-supervised training on Thursday after receiving punishment training and then Dido recommended the NTMC to dismiss all eight players. The Brazilian coach also stuck to his stance to terminate all eight players or lose him until meeting with Kazi Salahuddin, but he changed his mind after discussions with the BFF boss. "It is enough to say that we found a solution together," Dido said, "I came here to resign but after talking with the president, I honoured him." Asked whether the previous relation between coach and those players who walked out of the camp would prevail again, Salahuddin said, "A coach never keeps a good player out of the team whether he is furious with him." "Our players are professional and they will learn from the mistakes and the team will be training pr